<strong><code>HTMLDocument</code></strong> is an abstract interface which extends the <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/API/Document" title="The Document interface represents any web page loaded in the browser and serves as an entry point into the web page's content, which is the DOM tree.HTMLElement"><code>Document</code></a> interface to add HTML-specific features to the document object. It represents the root of the HTML document, within which its entire <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/API/Document_Object_Model">DOM</a> hierarchy resides.